#subtitle: Building relations with the other political parties of Germany.

= Inter-Party Relationships

The <span style="color: #c00000;">**SPD**</span> cannot govern by itself yet. Because we do not have an electoral majority, we need the support of other parties. Recently, our governments have consisted of the <span style="color: #c00000;">**Left Bloc**</span> of the <span style="color: #c00000;">**SPD**</span>, <span style="color: #BE3075;">**socialist**</span>, <span style="color: #FF7F00;">**christian**</span> and <span style="color: #E0B0FF;">**liberal**</span> parties. We can reach out and build additional connections with these parties, or perhaps we can stand alone.

- @liberals: Strengthen our bonds with the left-liberal <span style="color: #E0B0FF;">**Radical Democratic Party**</span>.
- @christian: Strengthen our bonds with the <span style="color: #000000;">**Christian People's Party**</span> and the <span style="color: #FF7F00;">**Christian Social Reich Party**</span>. 
- @lspd: Work towards repairing relationships with the <span style="color: #BE3075;">**Left Social Democratic Party**</span>.
- @spd_alone: The <span style="color: #c00000;">**SPD**</span> can stand alone for now.
- @easy_discard


@lspd
subtitle: -1 resources
choose-if: resources >= 1
unavailable-subtitle: Not enough resources.
on-arrival: resources -= 1; lspd_relation += 5; lspd_relation += 3 if left_strength > reformist_strength; lspd_relation -= 4 if in_april_coalition

We are improving relations with the <span style="color: #BE3075;">**socialists**</span>, who are the most skeptcist of their participation in the <span style="color: #c00000;">**Left Bloc**</span>. [? if left_strength > reformist_strength: With the <span style="color: #c00000;">**SPD**</span> being led by the left, our efforts prove themeselves much easier. ?] [? if in_april_coalition: Since the <span style="color: #BE3075;">**LSPD**</span> is excluded from government, they are way less trustful of us. ?]

@christian
subtitle: -1 resources
choose-if: resources >= 1
unavailable-subtitle: Not enough resources.
on-arrival: resources -= 1; csrp_relation += 5
go-to: christian_op if cvp_in_government = 1 and spd_in_government = 0 and chancellor != "Merz"; center_coalition if spd_in_government = 1 and cvp_in_government = 1; christian_merz if chancellor = "Merz"

@christian_op
on-arrival: cvp_relation += 5*(1 - dissent)

We are currently in opposition to the <span style="color: #000000;">**Center**</span>-led government, but that does not preclude the general building of feelings of good will. The <span style="color: #FF7F00;">**CSRP**</span> is easier to cooperate with, given their long history with us.

@christian_coalition
on-arrival: cvp_relation += 8*(1 - dissent)

We are currently coalition partners with the <span style="color: #000000;">**CVP**</span>, so improving relations comes naturally. The <span style="color: #FF7F00;">**CSRP**</span> is also easy to cooperate with, given their long history with us.

@christian_merz
on-arrival: cvp_relation += 5*(1 - dissent)

The Merz semi-autocratic regime makes building friendly relations with the <span style="color: #000000;">**CVP**</span> difficult, but not impossible. The <span style="color: #FF7F00;">**CSRP**</span> is easier to cooperate with, given their long history with us.

@liberals
